result.execSummary:
The defendant Eliza M Apfel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Eliza M Apfel is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Eliza M Apfel was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Eliza M Apfel was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Arraignment on December 9, 2014 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Eliza M Apfel in court with attorney Courtney J. Latzig.  Frederick Ian Bourg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Kyle Cadotte sworn and questioned by DA.  Sgt. with Red Cliff PD.  Obtained search warrant for Legendary Waters (specific rooms).  Witness identifies defendant.  Defendant was taken into custody when search warrant executed because of drug paraphernalia found.  Defendant did make a statement to Sgt. Cadotte and Inv. McKillip.  During booking process, Sgt. Cadotte was informed defendant was on a current bail/bond.  Exhibit #1 marked; Burnett County Bail/Bond for Burnett County case dated and signed 10-30-2014 by defendant.  Court receives exhibit #1.  Cross by Atty Latzig.  Pipe dropped from behind defendant in front of the officers executing search warrant.  Two investigators in the room defendant was in.  No re-direct by DA.
Argument by DA; asks for bind over.  Argument by Atty Latzig; asks for dismissal of felony charges.  Response by DA.  Court:  Satisfied there is probable cause on count 2, bound over on count 2.  Arraignment scheduled for December 9, 2014 at 01:00 pm.
